From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tim2tox-bootstrap <bootstrap@local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 20:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 15/15] V2TimConversation.fromJson: null-safe conv_recv_opt
 default

Symmetric with 0007 (V2TimMessage risk-type) and 0009 (V2TimGroupInfo)
null-safety patches: when the native FFI emits a partial conversation JSON
that omits `conv_recv_opt` (typical for newly-created conversations before
the user has set receive-message-options), `cReceiveMessageOpt2DartOpt(null)`
crashes because the enum-mapping helper unwraps the int.

Default the missing field to 0 (= ReceiveMessage) which matches the upstream
SDK's documented default for conversations without an explicit opt.

Field appears once in the source; the rewrite is the same one-liner trick
used in 0009 for V2TimGroupInfo fields. Filed as a separate patch (not
folded into 0009) to keep the 0009 hunk context untouched — the two files
are unrelated and bundling would mean reflowing the 0009 patch body.
---
 lib/models/v2_tim_conversation.dart | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/models/v2_tim_conversation.dart b/lib/models/v2_tim_conversation.dart
index d3ce7c3..b0630aa 100644
--- a/lib/models/v2_tim_conversation.dart
+++ b/lib/models/v2_tim_conversation.dart
@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@ class V2TimConversation {
     }
     unreadCount = json['conv_unread_num'];
     isPinned = json['conv_is_pinned'];
-    recvOpt = EnumUtils.cReceiveMessageOpt2DartOpt(json['conv_recv_opt']).index;
+    recvOpt = EnumUtils.cReceiveMessageOpt2DartOpt(json['conv_recv_opt'] ?? 0).index;
     orderkey = json['conv_active_time'];
     lastMessage = json['conv_last_msg'] != null
         ? V2TimMessage.fromJson(json['conv_last_msg'])
